<body>
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h1>Bali Jatra Fair</h1>
            <p>Celebrating Odisha's Maritime Heritage</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="contain">
        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Historical Significance</h2>
                <p>
                    Bali Jatra traces its roots to Odisha’s ancient maritime glory. Held on Kartik Purnima, it honors
                    the voyages of Odia traders to Southeast Asia. The fair symbolizes courage and enterprise, recalling
                    days when sailors braved the seas in wooden boats. Today, it’s a vibrant tribute to that legacy,
                    blending history with festivity.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Cultural Highlights</h2>
                <p>
                    The fair buzzes with cultural performances—Odissi dance, folk music, and theater—showcasing Odisha’s
                    rich heritage. Artisans display intricate crafts like Pattachitra paintings and silver filigree.
                    Visitors enjoy traditional songs and dances that echo the seafaring tales of old, making it a lively
                    celebration of identity and art.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Food and Cuisine</h2>
                <p>
                    Bali Jatra is a food lover’s delight. Stalls offer Odia delicacies like Chhena Poda, Pakhala Bhata,
                    and seafood specialties. Street vendors serve piping hot pithas (rice cakes) and spicy chaat. The
                    aroma of fresh jaggery sweets and roasted snacks fills the air, tempting every palate.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Shopping Experience</h2>
                <p>
                    Hundreds of stalls line the fair, selling handicrafts, textiles, and souvenirs. Shoppers find
                    handwoven sarees, palm leaf engravings, and brass figurines. Bargaining is part of the fun, with
                    vendors offering unique items that reflect Odisha’s craftsmanship. It’s a treasure trove for
                    collectors and tourists alike.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Festive Atmosphere</h2>
                <p>
                    The Mahanadi riverbank transforms into a festive hub during Bali Jatra. Colorful lights, boat races,
                    and children’s rides create a carnival vibe. Families gather to launch tiny paper boats, symbolizing
                    ancient voyages. The energy is infectious, uniting locals and visitors in joyous celebration.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar">
            <h2>Event Details</h2>
            <div class="details-grid">
